* A zoo food mixing problem with protein and fat requirements. Minimize cost by choosing how much of two food types to use, and interpret what an unbounded feasible region represents in this context.
* Analyzing whether an unbounded region can have both a maximum and minimum value, classifying the statement as sometimes, always, or never true.
* Identifying which of four graphed systems of inequalities does not match the others. (Images of the four graphs are provided in the original worksheet.)
* Explaining how two different vertices could yield the same maximum value for a linear objective function over a correctly graphed bounded region.
